  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Male or female subjects aged ≥ 18 years and ≤ 85 years.

          -  Subjects with acute non-infectious anterior uveitis with onset of symptoms within the
             previous 2 weeks.

          -  Best corrected visual acuity (BCVA) better than or equal to 35 letters in the study
             eye and 65 letters in the non-study eye using ETDRS testing.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Have severe/serious ocular pathology in the study eye(s) which may preclude study
             completion, in the judgement of the Investigator.

          -  Active intermediate or posterior uveitis in the study eye(s).

          -  Previous anterior uveitis episode in the study eye ≤ 4 weeks prior to screening.

          -  Have participated in another investigational device or drug study within 30 days prior
             to screening.

          -  Participation in a prior ADX-102 study.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
